featured_reviews.review_id:
A beautiful and a vast masjid located at the heart(centre) of the udupi city. With facilities of drinking water, wudu, toilet and largest parking facility for prayees. Also there is a big pond having clean water and some fishes in it as a part of decor.
Also drinking water facility for market people at entrance gate of masjid.It's iconic in this place. I love the architecture of this masjid.
With a capacity of accommodating almost 3000 prayees/worshipers and built over two acres of land and built with spacious prayers halls spanning 18,000 square feet, the district's largest mosque, JAMIA MASJID UDUPI.

The inaugural ceremony of the mosque was held on Friday, August 10 2012 at 12.15 pm. An Iftar gathering was hosted on Friday evening.

The Masjid stands three-storeys tall, with the basement comprising of a prayer hall separate for women capable of accommodating 400 women at a time with the ground floor being the main prayer hall. The complex also includes a parking area.

*Seperate prayer room for Ladies.
*All types of precautions taken for covid19.
*Having seperate office to maintain masjid.

featured_reviews.review_id: Jamia Masjid is the largest mosque in the district, housed in a three-storey building. The basement spans 5,200 square feet, ground floor 6,000 square feet and first floor 4,500 square feet.  Bangalore-based Sajjad Associates are the architects, and construction has been carried out by Udupi-based S N Construction.

Architecture is really very appreciable!
Very neat and clean mosque in Manipal !
